OL,3,CTravel compensation and penalties:
OL,4,CWhat are your rights amid global IT
OL,5,Coutage?
OL,7,FIf you are affected by the outage and
OL,8,Fyou think you are not going to be able
OL,9,Fto make a regular payment, in the
OL,10,Ffirst instance you should contact the
OL,11,Forganisation you owe money to inform
OL,12,Fthem about the problem. and ask if you
OL,13,Fcan delay the payment.
OL,15,FBut, "if you can't do that, we advise
OL,16,Fkeeping receipts any costs incurred,
OL,17,Fsay penalty charges for missing a
OL,18,Fpayment and taking those to your bank
OL,19,Flater," Sam Richardson Deputy Editor
OL,20,Fof Which? Money told ITV News.
